

1. activate qiime2 in wsl environment

conda activate qiime2-amplicon-2025.7

2. Setting working directory

cd "/mnt/d/OneDrive/qiime/yesid_raw data/zr25695.rawdata.250827"

3. create the manifest.tsv file (this file will be used as a list during qiime step)
( \
  echo -e "sample-id\tforward-absolute-filepath\treverse-absolute-filepath"; \
  paste \
    <(ls *R1.fastq.gz | sort -V) \
    <(ls *R2.fastq.gz | sort -V) \
  | awk -v path="$(pwd)/" '{OFS="\t"; print "sample-"NR, path$1, path$2}' \
) > manifest.tsv

4. verify the file

head -n 3 manifest.tsv

5. import data into qiime 2

qiime tools import \
  --type 'SampleData[PairedEndSequencesWithQuality]' \
  --input-path manifest.tsv \
  --output-path paired-end-demux.qza \
  --input-format PairedEndFastqManifestPhred33V2

6. using paired-end-demux.qza to check file quality

qiime demux summarize \
  --i-data paired-end-demux.qza \
  --o-visualization demux.qzv

7. using demux.qzv file, to check the quality of file quality (sequencing quality)

go to this website "https://view.qiime2.org/"
open the tab "interative quality plot"
the data y value (quality score) is lower than 25 is suck


